    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Please stop with the disinformation.<br /> The workers did not Balk they were not permitted, and probably for good reason.<br /> Sadly the man with the power washer who cleaned the puke from the parking lot had no safety gear, none, he was not qualified. No one informed him that as from 1 to 10 organisms in a microscopic particle of water kicked up from his pressure washer could infect, could kill, not just him but anyone in the area. No one trained him that the organisms could have survived for days. More likely people like yourself have repeatedly taught him that the Ebola virus is not transmissible airborne. Sounds good, but it is a deceptively deadly phrase. Ebola is transmissible as an aerosol which means in a droplet of water, like a sneeze or power washed puke spray.<br /> Airborne has the specific meaning of carried dry on a piece of dust.</p> 
<p>People will die if you do not educate them in the truth. Selling relaxants wholesale will kill people. There is no need for Americans to die from Ebola. Truly it will be willful ignorance which does them in.</p>

