    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>This article praises Presbyterian Hospital, and perhaps rightly. However, the article takes on a “reassuring tone”, as if to indicate that our medical system is capable of dealing with an outbreak of ebola. The cases were individual, and circumstances were controlled. As stated in the article, there are only 5 such isolation units in the US. If ebola were to turn up in a major urban center, such as New York, or L.A., there would be absolutely no way to manage the contact list, and the infection could easily spread rapidly. The spread could overwhelm any efforts to contain it.</p>

    	</div>



    	<div class="comment_controls" data-called-out-state="off">
