    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>Off the big-media record, Ebola virologists apparently by reliable googled sources are expressing how much they don’t know about this apparently mutating version of Ebola now in the U.S. It could mutate to have a longer-than 21-day incubation period, of course it could, and to be less (or even more deadly) in humans, while being transmitted by air — google the science off the CDC party line and you’ll see for yourself. Airborne particles are apparently already known to be released by the Ebola virus during bodily fluid emissions (projectile vomiting definitely, perhaps even sneezing and coughing), and nobody yet knows to what extent humans are being infected this way. The nurse in Spain with Ebola this week? By the media-sponsored spin, there should be no way she was infected. Thus the U.S. science experiment will likely answer scientific questions, for sure, while U.S. citizens suffer horribly and die.<br /> How does it feel to be a U.S. citizen where the handwriting on the wall is that the U.S. government is willing for the U.S. citizenry to be the UN WHO’s health experiment? Keep letting Ebola in here and then, with the U.S. governmental funds (unavailable to the same extent in W. Africa despite U.S. troops going there to “fight Ebola”), all the unanswered virologists’ questions can be answered about contagion vectors among trackable U.S. populations, speed of viral mutation, transmission by aerosolized particles from sneezing and other bodily fluid emissions of the Ebola-contaminated, and which U.S. lower animal populations will serve as carrier reservoir populations of Ebola between human outbreaks. (Factory-farmed pigs and chickens for human food are already indicated as Ebola reservoir animals by extrapolation from Canadian Public Health studies. Once an Ebola pandemic dies down on a continent among the humans, the carrier lower animal populations harbor it asymptomatically, as monkeys who sometimes are eaten as bush meat in Africa, then causing another human outbreak. At least this is what virologists seem to know now before the science-project results on U.S. citizens as Ebola guinea pigs are in.)</p>

    	</div>



