        <li data-comment-id="comment_blogAndPostId/blog/comment/2238-3371-859" data-comment-wp-id="859"  parent-id="" class="comment level0 calledOut" data-badges-advoice="">
            <div class="entity_block">
                <a class="avatar" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/ronanthony/">
                    <img src="http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/deac86a6b2a6cc0fdd5b03d14f1e1a97?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G" alt="Ron Anthony" />
                </a>



                <a class="user_name" href="http://blogs.forbes.com/people/ronanthony/">
                    Ron Anthony
                </a>


   		<span class="timestamp">3 months ago</span>
    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		
<p>The good news is that the hospitals with Biosafety level 4 beds have a perfect record on a small sampling of treatment. The bad news is that there are only about 19 of these beds in the US.</p> 
<p>Our hospitals as a whole have a less than perfect record in dealing with other infections like MRSA so there is reason to be very concerned for what might happen if the Biosafety level 4 hospitals are overwhelmed.</p> 
<p>How could that happen? First, there is the CDC’s 21 day rule that the WHO says is only 95% accurate. The next big surprise might be someone cleared on the 21 day rule and then developing Ebola and thinking it is the flu. This person could then go home and try to ride it out or worse yet work while it is developing. That nightmare could really spread the illness.</p> 
<p>Second, we are sending 4,000 troops to Liberia. They are not supposed to get involved with treatment of Ebola, but they could get close. There is a lot of unknown and will be plenty of chance for errors in the projected runaway environment that they will be entering.</p> 
<p>We don’t have that much room for error with Ebola. Our military involvement in Liberia could be a disaster. We must not trust our “experts” blindly especially when they don’t agree. For more on this visit: http://reorganizehealthcare.com/beware-of-experts/</p>

    	</div>



